<br>
When you talk of them being a far cry from our board in the banning departments it's because you are comparing apples and oranges<br>
<br>
1. I am wagering (i could be completely off base here) that that was NOT their rant section, which is where most of our ban problems come in. And furthermore We here tend to move posts from general to rants based on one fucktard cursing. Other places dont move the whole post, they leave it in &quot;general&quot; and then ban the one fucktard - in this case shadow (not cursing but other rules and also not commenting on shadow being a fucktard, just the jist of what happending)<br>
<br>
2. i assume they are a &quot;bigger/popular&quot; forum which does change things...the bigger you get - not just readers but posters - the more you can afford to boot and boot. Look at the rogue's forums The Safehouse, they boot in a heartbeat. But if you are a small forums and you boot too many people pretty soon there is only one person posting..../shrug. It's a catch 22, gotta put up with some sucko posts to have content, or boot people and have better content but risk ending up with not enough content.<br>
<br>
3. The person &quot;modding&quot; the forum may be the same person that started it/owns it etc which is different than our somewhat more democratic ways of picking mods who dont really have anything invested except perhaps time or donations...which could lend itself to different ways of handling things...the guy could be putting out cash every month and really not give a shit how it ends up as long as he has his say and feels like HE is getting his money's worth.<br>
<br>
etc<br>
etc<br>
etc<br>
